      • addToCompleted

        public void addToCompleted(ProcessedImport task)
        Updates the batch status to reflect that the specified import has completed either successfully or with a failure depending on the value returned by ProcessedImport.succeeded(). This method will check that all the following conditions are true:
        • The queued task is that of an import in the batch.
        • If this method was previously called with an argument t, then task.succeeded() == t.succeeded(). In other words, you can call this method multiple times for the same import task as long as the specified import outcome is always the same.
        If any of the above is false, then an exceptions is thrown and the status is not updated.
        Parameters:
        task - the import.
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if the argument is null.
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if any of the above conditions are not met.
